The paper deals with network models and propagation mechanisms, which are common topics in the fields of social networks (cs.SI), network science (cs.SD), and network economics (cs.NE). The use of the Kleinberg's small-world network model and the study of routing time suggest that the paper may also fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
